<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-12T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/449: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-12T15:00:00-04:00">May 12, 1939—3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>17. Your 31, May 10, 6 p.m. Please telegraph complete text of <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> given to you by the Liberian
                                Secretary of State on May 10. The Department would also appreciate
                                receiving by telegraph the text of the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> submitted to the Liberian Government by the
                                French Chargé d’Affaires on May 8.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>